        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 28 at 4:59PM CDT until April 28 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Solomon, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters. At 4:55 PM CDT, a spotter in
Solomon reported hail up to the size of ping pong balls.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Wakefield, Abilene, Chapman, Moonlight, Talmage, Solomon, and
Enterprise.

This includes Interstate 70 between mile markers 267 and 289.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for central,
northeastern and east central Kansas.

Prepare immediately for large hail and damaging winds. People outside
should move to a shelter, inside a strong building and away from
windows.</instruction>
